<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[192,1441,547,1883]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,388,1667,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2008" box="[626,688,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Efferia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinei">
<emphasis box="[626,688,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">hinei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, genitive case, is in recognition of the significant contributions of the American dipterist J. H. Hine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
